ommunity the state of israel and various medical institutions committed to research after all that is his family’s heritage fleeing communist cuba when the young oscar was only  year old his parents found refuge and later fortune on the shores of miami beach fla his father became very active in the latin division of the area’s jewish federation and soon became its president holding meetings at the family home today the younger feldenkreis sitting in his house overlooking biscayne bay in miami recounts listening to his father at the meetings and participating in the federation dinners as a young boy he now holds a cabinet position at the greater miami jewish federation and each year he tries to donate more money than the year before “being successful you have to be able to share and our family is very big on that — on being able to give back as much as possible” feldenkreis said “we’re very much involved in jewish causes where i would say we give a big percentage of our donations” each year feldenkreis donates tens of thousands of dollars to miami’s jewish federation he also purchases vast amounts of israel bonds to help bolster israel’s economy and he is contributing to the funding of the expansion of temple menorah in miami beach his nonjewish philanthropic efforts include donations to the university of miamijackson memorial hospital feldenkreis contributes to these organizations as a private individual and not on behalf of perry ellis though he is driven to expand the business not so much for his own personal benefit but rather to increase his ability to give with his philanthropic goals in mind failure has never been an option for feldenkreis in fact it’s failure that he fears “i think that businessmen that have that type of fear will always be successful because they are going to try as hard as possible to make sure that they do not fail” feldenkreis said perry ellis international achieved a great measure of success and expansion under his leadership when feldenkreis joined his father’s apparel business in  he started a pants line that he called feldini an italian spinoff of his last name and he started developing what he calls “the bottom business” with the same levelheaded practicality that he exuded during our interview feldenkreis recognized that the average american consumer did not want to pay  to  for pants made in italy he then realized that there was an opportunity to develop pants manufactured in korea that made of  wool or woolen blends would sell for only  to  it was this move that put the company in a relationship with federated department stores which in its day comprised the large department stores that dominated the apparel industry the momentum grew from there feldenkreis was responsible for the company’s tremendous growth spurt during the s with profits rising to  million in  from  million only a year earlier he and his father decided to take the company public on the nasdaq exchange turning the company’s fortunes then  million to an astonishing  million in one year’s time “we started to grow almost  every single year” feldenkreis said in  the company acquired its first true brands and today it boasts a composite of such familiar labels as perry ellis manhattan john henry mundo del marco axis and treaco st rafael to name a few perry ellis international is also the licensee for pga tour golf and holds the license for all categories of nike swimwear feldenkreis is always on the move seeking out new opportunities for his miamiheadquartered company with multiple offices in asia and on both american coasts “our culture is very entrepreneurial we’re about growth” he said no one can say that feldenkreis is all work and no play to the contrary he can be spotted each hanukkah in aspen colo with his wife of  years and their three daughters ranging in age from  to  “we light hanukkah candles in aspen” he said the five family members also enjoy boating and they travel to europe together during the summers when at home they enjoy traditional sabbath dinners and keep kosher feldenkreis said with pride having attended hebrew academy of miami beach feldenkreis is a strong believer in passing down jewish values to his children who attended jewish day schools in fact he begins each day by donning tefillin feldenkreis is very active at temple menorah a large wellestablished conservative synagogue in miami beach as a board member he serves on a committee charged with building an updated synagogue and a new social hall “for the last  years i have been doing the israel bonds campaign drive at temple menorah” he said feldenkreis recently ascended the podium as the honored guest of the  israel bonds dinner where he spoke about the complex issues facing israel today and in the future “it’s a very troublesome situation” feldenkreis said describing the challenges that israel faces and the breadth of israel’s enemies which he said reach far beyond the palestinians his commitment to israel is well evidenced from  through  feldenkreis served as chairman of miami’s israelamerica chamber of commerce helping businesspeople look for opportunities to import and export products between the united states and israel “i think the biggest issue we have within the israelamerica chamber of commerce is that we need more people involved” he said “the local israelis that have been very successful here should be much more involved” one of his personal goals is to take a more active role in federation activities “i believe as an american jew that i have to give a big percentage of our commitments to the jewish federation and support for the state of israel” feldenkreis explained he urges others to do the same “the us will continue to support the state of israel… as long as it sees a strong zionistamerican movement for the support of israel on a philanthropic basis i think that there is a lot of need for american jews that are not involved and have the power and the wherewithal to be able to give back to the state of israel” he asserted “i believe that that’s something that we need to work on” the forwards independent journalism depends on donations from readers like you give now author soriya daniels email facebook google twitter recommended for you explore more sign up for our newsletters thank you you are now signed up to receive our newsletters recommended for you follow the author we’ll email you whenever we publish another article by jj goldberg thank you close recommend this article giving back a family tradition from send to  add another add a message send me a copy thank you this article has been sent close thank you perry ellis boss is a racist homophobe executive says  new york post thanks for contacting us weve received your submission back to reading news metro page six sports business opinion entertainment fashion living media tech real estate sub menu  video photos covers columnists horoscopes sub menu  email newsletters home delivery sign in latest in business tobacco stocks plunge as fda eyes nicotine clampdown shkrelis lawyer compares case to throwing pizza at a wall meg whitman says she wont be ubers next ceo barbie sales are bombing despite new body types the pressure on snap shares is about to get worse starbucks shares plummet on fears that us growth is slowing procter  gamble rejects nelson peltzs help halliburton pays m to settle africa bribe probe offprice retailers are losing their steam amazons second quarter hits  percent below projections adidas unloads iconic hockey brand ccm for m jeff bezos reign as the worlds richest person was shortlived share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy business share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy perry ellis boss is a racist homophobe executive says by josh saul view author archive get author rss feed namerequired emailrequired commentrequired october    pm modal trigger oscar feldenkreis wireimage more on perry ellis kansas senior star has the worst game at worst possible time chemistry beats talent no  kansas rolls past maryland perry ellis chairman considers selling his clothing company perry ellis settles explosive lawsuit alleging racism homophobia a new lawsuit claims the ​coo of perry ellis ​international ​is a racist homophobe who told underlings to make sure there are “no blacks in my ads” or “anyone who looked too gay​” oscar feldenkreis the son of perry ellis international ​founder ​george feldenkreis allegedly ​made the hateful remarks to a gay senior executive joseph cook  who filed the lawsuit in manhattan federal court wednesday “mr cook has been forced to endure highly offensive homophobic racial and ethnic slurs by mr feldenkreis” the suit ​claims adding that feldenkreis is slated to succeed his father as ceo next year despite his blatently discriminatory beliefs “these include but are not limited to admonishing mr cook and his team to make sure there are ‘no blacks in my ads’ or ‘anyone who looked too gay’ and telling mr cook he could easily avoid jury service by ‘telling them you hate n—–s and f–s’” ​​cooks also says in the suit that the racism came up when he was working to approve a lord  taylor print ad with an underling comparing a model’s skin tone to a black crayola crayon according to the suit cook claims that when he complained about the discrimination the company retaliated against him with a campaign designed to isolate and exclude him ​​“i am deeply saddened as a gay man and someone who has always been proud of who i am no matter my color or sexual orientation that a company executive could be so intolerant of others” cook said in a statement provided by his lawyer douglas wigdor “i hope this lawsuit will change the views of leadership at perry ellis and bring them into the st century” ​​the suit names both feldenkreis and perry ellis ​international ​as defendants and seeks unspecified damages ​perry ellis denied cook’s claims in a statement “perry ellis is a company that promotes equal opportunity and a positive working environment the company is proud of the fact that it is probably one of the most diverse companies in the apparel business following its multicultural roots stemming from puerto rico and cuba” the statement read “perry ellis categorically denies any allegations to the contrary the claims that have been asserted will be vigorously defended against” share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy filed under lawsuits   perry ellis share this article share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy read next advertisers probe agencies over kickbacks backroom deals read next advertisers probe agencies over kickbacks backroom deals share selection columnists john crudele if janet yellen is acting worried — you should be too nicole gelinas  ways to make flying great again keith j kelly playboy cut partner out of logo licensing deal suit see all columnists trending nowin business  jeff bezos reign as the worlds richest person was shortlived  jeff bezos is the richest person in the world  amazons second quarter hits  percent below projections now on chester bennington’s widow ‘i lost my soul mate’ priyanka chopra developing abc series about bollywood star britney and justin’s best look ever is now a very pricey tshirt see all video  helpless hamster is tossed around like a pile of laundry more stories page six george and amal clooneys twins revealed now on decider how do eunuchs have sex and other important game of thrones questions answered nypost couple caught in financial spiral jump to their deaths news corp is a network of leading companies in the world of diversified media news and information services news corp harpercollins marketwatch realtorcom dow jones the sun storyful wall street journal the times mansion global new york post the australian checkout news america marketing newscomau unruly send to email address your name your email address cancel post was not sent  check your email addresses em